<paragraph blockId="118.[151,1436,784,1313]" box="[199,723,1000,1025]" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,282,1000,1025]" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">Range.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[289,350,1000,1025]" name="Chile" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">Chile</collectingCountry>
(Region XV). See also 
<figureCitation box="[617,719,1000,1025]" captionStart="FIGURE46" captionStartId="90.[151,250,1529,1551]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1508]" captionTargetId="figure@90.[151,1436,193,1508]" captionTargetPageId="90" captionText="FIGURE46.Geographic distribution by Colletes species.(A) C.nigropilosus n. sp. and C.musculus; (B) C.ventricarinatusn. sp., C. quelu and C. nigritulus; (C) C.simulatus n. sp., C. sulcatus and C. toroi n. sp. Scale bars approximately 300 km." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1116104/files/figure.png" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">Fig. 46B</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="118.[151,1436,784,1313]" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,534,1036,1061]" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">Biogeographic distribution.</emphasis>
South American transition zone (Desert and 
<collectingRegion box="[1083,1183,1037,1061]" country="Chile" name="Atacama" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">Atacama</collectingRegion>
provinces). Northern Chilean species distributed in the summer rainfall area at altitudes of 
<quantity box="[928,1076,1072,1097]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.35" metricValueMax="3.6" metricValueMin="3.1" pageId="118" pageNumber="119" unit="m" value="3350.0" valueMax="3600.0" valueMin="3100.0">3100–3600m</quantity>
a.s.l.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="118.[151,1436,784,1313]" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,374,1108,1133]" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">DNA barcode.</emphasis>
Available. BOLD: ACK8653 (3♂♂). Distance from the nearest neighbour (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Friese" authorityYear="1910" box="[1273,1419,1108,1133]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="118" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigritulus">
<emphasis box="[1273,1419,1108,1133]" italics="true" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">C. nigritulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
): 7.29–7.71%.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="118.[151,1436,784,1313]" box="[199,472,1180,1205]" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,347,1180,1205]" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">Floral hosts.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
